<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Biologica Nyssana" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="17 - 20" refId="B35" refString="Pesic, V, Gloeer, P, 2012. A new species of Bythiospeum Bourguignat, 1882 (Hydrobiidae, Gastropoda) from Montenegro. Biologica Nyssana 3: 17 - 20" title="A new species of Bythiospeum Bourguignat, 1882 (Hydrobiidae, Gastropoda) from Montenegro." volume="3" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
described a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bourguignat" authorityYear="1882" class="Gastropoda" family="Moitessieriidae" genus="Bythiospeum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bythiospeum" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Bythiospeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bourguignat, 1882: 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. bogici" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="bogici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">B. bogici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
, 2012 from underground waters of Vrelo 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Taban”">&quot;Taban&quot;</normalizedToken>
, in central Montenegro. Their description was based on empty shells. Later they (
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="565 - 566" refId="B36" refString="Pesic, V, Gloeer, P, 2013. Montenegrospeum, a new genus of hydrobiid snails (Gastropoda: Rissooidea) from Montenegro. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 65: 565 - 566" title="Montenegrospeum, a new genus of hydrobiid snails (Gastropoda: Rissooidea) from Montenegro." volume="65" year="2013">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) collected live specimens, and described the lack of eyes and pigment and the penis with a lobe at its medial part. They considered 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. bogici" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="bogici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">B. bogici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as belonging to a new genus: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Gloer" authorityYear="2013" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Montenegrospeum" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Montenegrospeum" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Montenegrospeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
, 2013. Later, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.022.023" author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B17" refString="Falniowski, A, Pesic, V, Gloeer, P, 2014. Montenegrospeum Pesic &amp; Gloeer, 2013: a representative of Moitessieriidae? Folia Malacologica 22: 263-268. https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.022.023" title="Montenegrospeum Pesic &amp; Gloeer, 2013: a representative of Moitessieriidae? Folia Malacologica 22: 263 - 268." url="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.022.023" year="2014">Falniowski et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated with molecular data that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Gloer" authorityYear="2013" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Montenegrospeum" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Montenegrospeum" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Montenegrospeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Hydrobiidae</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bourguignat" authorityYear="1863" class="Gastropoda" family="Moitessieriidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Moitessieriidae</taxonomicName>
, despite striking similarity of the shell between this snail and e.g., 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Iglica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iglica" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Iglica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 1927. Numerous live specimens of this species were pumped from interstitial habitats at the localities 1, 7 and 21 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution of the studied taxa. Localities' numbers correspond to Table 1." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1047.64034.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/560476" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
